data.title: Kim Kardashian reveals her wedding plans and qualities she is seeking in her life partner
data.meta_description: Kim Kardashian, 43, in a recent episode of The Kardashians spoke about her plans of settling down again. Despite being a three-time divorcée, Kim affirmed her belief in love, and in a previous interview, she hinted at an age limit for her future partner, expressing contentment with her current single status.
data.text:
Synopsis

Kim Kardashian, 43, in a recent episode of The Kardashians spoke about her plans of settling down again. Despite being a three-time divorcée, Kim affirmed her belief in love, and in a previous interview, she hinted at an age limit for her future partner, expressing contentment with her current single status.

Kim Kardashian is embraced to the single life for now and has no plans for dating for at least the next year, the reality star revealed in a recent episode of Kardashians. The reality star, now 43 and mother of four, discussed her dating plans with her hairstylist Chris Appleton while en route to Las Vegas for a wedding, according to People's magazine. When asked if she had another wedding in her future, Kim admitted to being undecided, oscillating between the idea of settling down again or remaining single.

Chris, who has known Kim for a long time, pointed out that she seems to be in the best place she's ever been, praising her control over various aspects of her life, including her children and business. Kim attributed her current state of contentment to being in a calm place and suggested that it might be a good time to invite positive energy into her life.

Despite her commitment to staying single, Kim has a manifest list of qualities she desires in a future partner: The list includes someone who both calms her and excites her, values privacy, and encourages personal growth. Kim acknowledged that her list is continuously evolving, and she won't settle until her partner fulfills every criterion.

Reflecting on love after attending Chris and Lukas's wedding, Kim, a three-time divorcée, affirmed her belief in love and the joy of falling for someone.

Kim was previously married to music producer Damon Thomas, NBA player Kris Humphries, and rapper Kanye West, with whom she shares four children: North, Saint, Chicago, and Psalm.

Earlier in an interview, Kim Kardashian had also hinted at an age limit for her future life partner. "I have age limits, guys. I need just a little more age-appropriate. I need [someone in their] 40s," she said.

Kim Kardashian's personal wealth is pegged at $1.7 billion, according to Forbes, the bulk of which is attributed from her stake from her stake in Skims, her shapewear and clothing business.
